                                Credentials credentials,

Parameters:

credentials - the Credentials to connect with (or null to attempt to use the best available credentials)

close

public void close()
Description copied from class: TFSConnection

This Closable interface method must be called when this TFSConnection instance is no longer needed. This method cleans up resources associated with this instance. After calling this method, this instance should be discarded.

After calling TFSConnection.close(), no methods on a TFSConnection instance should be subsequently called. The TFSConnection.close() method should only be called once; subsequent calls to TFSConnection.close() will log a warning and do nothing. See TFSConnection.isClosed(). Subsequent calls to other methods will throw TFSConnectionClosedExceptions.

This method should not be called on a closed TFSConnection .

Specified by:
close in interface com.microsoft.tfs.util.Closable
Overrides:
close in class TFSConnection
